====Derived terms====
*[[പള്ളീലച്ഛന്]]..........Christian priest.
*[[വല്ല്യച്ഛന്]]..........Older paternal uncle. Literally "big father".
*[[കൊച്ചച്ഛന്]]..........Younger paternal uncle. Literally "small father".
====Synonyms====

*[[പിതാവു&#3405;]]..........This word was derived from Sanskrit ''pitā'' and is considered very formal.
*[[തന്ത]]..........This is ɚ very colloquial and rude term meaning father.
*[[ബാപ്പ]]..........This is the word that most Muslims who speak Malayalam use for father.
*[[അപ്പന്]]''or'' [[അപ്പച്ചന്]].......... These are usually used by Christiɚns who use അച്ഛന് to refer to priests (with irregular vocative അച്ഛോ [ɚtʃtʃhoː] most of the time).

